<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<assessmentItem xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1
    http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1.xsd" identifier="T007.04" title="Test 7.04: Table
    Elements" adaptive="false" timeDependent="false">
    <stylesheet href="tableElements.css" type="text/css"/>
    <itemBody>
        <p>This test uses col and colgroup elements to group cells by column.  In the default
        style, the table should look the same as the one in Test 7.02, but without the caption.
        For systems that support CSS the 3 columns should have red, green and blue backgrounds
        (from left to right).</p>
        <table>
            <colgroup class="left"/>
            <colgroup>
                <col class="middle"/>
                <col class="right"/>
            </colgroup>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <th/>
                    <th>Col 1</th>
                    <th>Col 2</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <th>Row A</th>
                    <td>A1</td>
                    <td>A2</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <th>Row B</th>
                    <td>B1</td>
                    <td>B2</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>Note that this example will not validate against the QTI 2.0 schema due to a bug in that
        specification concerning the span attribute.</p>
    </itemBody>
</assessmentItem>
